The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 November is 100,066 (11,533.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 November, there were 3,728 new confirmed cases (429.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 31 October, there were 4,818 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 23% (1,090 fewer cases).
